<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Jokbal</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 kg pig's trotters (jokbal)</li>
            <li>1 cup soy sauce</li>
            <li>1/2 cup rice wine</li>
            <li>1/4 cup sugar</li>
            <li>1/4 cup honey</li>
            <li>1/4 cup minced garlic</li>
            <li>2 teaspoons minced ginger</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon black pepper</li>
            <li>5 cups water</li>
            <li>1 bunch green onions, chopped</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon sesame oil</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon sesame seeds, toasted</li>
            <li>1 cucumber, sliced (for garnish)</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>pork</li>
            <li>korean</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Clean the pig's trotters thoroughly and remove any hair. Rinse them under cold water.</li>
            <li>In a large pot, combine soy sauce, rice wine, sugar, honey, minced garlic, minced ginger, black pepper, and water.</li>
            <li>Bring the mixture to a boil and add the pig's trotters. Reduce the heat to low and simmer for 2-3 hours until the trotters are tender.</li>
            <li>Once the trotters are tender, remove them from the pot and let them cool slightly.</li>
            <li>Preheat the oven to 200°C (392°F).</li>
            <li>Place the trotters on a baking sheet and brush them with the cooking liquid. Bake for 20-30 minutes until the trotters develop a nice glaze.</li>
            <li>Meanwhile, in a bowl, mix chopped green onions with sesame oil.</li>
            <li>Once the jokbal is ready, garnish it with the green onion mixture, toasted sesame seeds, and cucumber slices.</li>
            <li>Serve hot and enjoy your delicious Jokbal!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

